CONFIGURATION
=============

There are many environment variables note uses to configure itself
plugins can have their own set of configuration variables too.

to get a list of all command line options just run note with no
arguments.

VARIABLE NAME   DEFAULT VALUE         CLI    DESCRITPION
===================================================================
NOTE_PATH       "$HOME/notes"         -d     jekyll is run here
PRIVATE         ""                    -p     make this note private
NOTE_EDITOR     [git config]          -e     editor to use
CONF_BLK        "default"             -c     .noterc configuration block
JEKYLL_BIN      "jekyll"              -b     jekyll binary
DEBUG           ""                    -v     debug level verbosity
MARKDOWN        "textile"             -m     markdown (file extension)
dogit           "i"                   -g     how to run git y/n/a/i
dojekyll        "i"                   -j     how to run jekyll
default_category "notes"                     default category
layout          "note"                       default layout
published       "false"                      publish note by default?

you can manipulate any of the many environment variables that note uses
internally using one or more of the "hooks" (see EXTEND for more)
